<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="1111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1111">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">393.115/9–2149: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Consul at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">McConaughy</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-21T15:00:00-04:00">September 21,
                                1949—3 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1940. Urgently request full report all facts bearing on allegations made by
                        Chinese Foreign Office stated Cantel 1134, Sep 21 to Dept, rptd Shanghai
                        542. Include all pertinent entries both vessels logs and other info which
                        masters can supply. Make available immed and without comment to
                        Isbrandtsen’s reps Hong Kong and Shanghai statements made by Chen reftel.
                        Action latter Hong Kong and Shanghai respectively.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>